  <header class="hero">
    <h1>Understanding Compound Measures</h1>
    <p>In this lesson,we will explore the concenpt of Compound Measures in mathematics which includes:</p>
    <p>Speed, Density and Pressure</p>
  </header>

  <div class="topic-nav">
      <button onclick="showSection('overview')">Overview</button>
      <button onclick="showSection('speed')">Speed</button>
      <button onclick="showSection('density')">Density</button>
      <button onclick="showSection('pressure')">Pressure</button>
  </div>

  <section id="overview" class="topic-section">
    <section>
    <header class="formula1">
      <h1>Compound Measures
     </h1>
     <p>Here we will learn about compound measures including speed, density and pressure and look at problem solving using compound measures.
     </p>
     <p>There are also compound measures worksheets based on Edexcel, AQA and OCR exam questions, along with further guidance on where to go next if you’re still stuck.</p>  
    </header>
    <p>Compound measures are calculations made by combining two different measurements.And also are measurements that combine two different quantities to create a new value.</p>
    <p>They are commonly used in mathematics, science and everyday life.</p>
    <p>The most common compound measures at GCSE level are:
 </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Speed = Distance ÷ Time</li>
    <li>Density = Mass ÷ Volume</li>
    <li>Pressure = Force ÷ Area</li>
  </ul> </p>
  </section>
  <section>
    <header class="formula2">
      <h1>What are compound measures?
     </h1>
     <p>Compound measures are measures which are found from two other measures.
     </p>
     <p>The most common compound measures studied in GCSE maths are speed, density, and pressure.</p>
     <p>To calculate the value of a compound measure, we need to know the value and the units of the other two measures</p>  
    </header>
  </section>

    <section id="concept">
        <h2>What Is It?</h2>
        <p><strong>Speed</strong> measures how fast something moves.</p>
        <p><strong>Density</strong> measures how compact a material is.</p>
        <p><strong>Pressure</strong> measures how force is spread over an area.</p>
        <p>
    They are called "compound" because they combine two quantities into one new measurement.
  </p>
    </section>

    <section id="formula">
        <h2>Formula Box</h2>
        <div class="formula-box">
            <p>Speed = Distance ÷ Time</p>
            <p>Density = Mass ÷ Volume</p>
            <p>Pressure = Force ÷ Area</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="examples">
        <h2>Worked Examples</h2>

        <div class="card">
            <p><strong>Example 1:</strong> A car travels 120 km in 2 hours.</p>
            <p>Speed = 120 ÷ 2 = 60 km/h</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <p><strong>Example 2:</strong> Mass = 500g, Volume = 100cm³</p>
            <p>Density = 500 ÷ 100 = 5 g/cm³</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <p><strong>Example 3:</strong> Force = 200N, Area = 10m²</p>
            <p>Pressure = 200 ÷ 10 = 20 N/m²</p>
        </div> 
        <div class="diagram-box">

  <table>

  <tr>
  <th>Measure</th>
  <th>What It Compares</th>
  <th>Example</th>
  </tr>

  <tr>
  <td>Speed</td>
  <td>Distance and Time</td>
  <td>60 km in 1 hour = 60 km/h</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
     <td>Density</td>
     <td>Mass and Volume</td>
     <td>500 g ÷ 100 cm³ = 5 g/cm³</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
  <td>Pressure</td>
  <td>Force and Area</td>
  <td>200 N ÷ 10 m² = 20 N/m²</td>
  </tr>

  </table>

  </div>

  <p>
      These formulas help us understand how different physical quantities are related.
      They are widely used in science, engineering and everyday problem solving.
  </p>
    </section>
    </section>

  <section id="speed" class="topic-section">
    <section >
        <header class="formulaS">
            <h2>SPEED</h2>
        <p><strong>Speed</strong> Is a compound measure made from dividing a unit of distance by a unit of time. Speed is therefore a measure of how much an object has travelled over a certain time period.</p>
        <P>Common units for speed include metres per second (m/s)
            (m/s) and kilometres per hour (k m / h).(km/h). Miles per hour (m p h) (mph) is associated with the speed of a vehicle. At GCSE we tend to use metric units rather than imperial units.</P>
        </header>
        <p>
    It compares the <strong>distance travelled</strong> with the <strong>time taken</strong>.
    If an object travels a large distance in a short time, it has a higher speed.
    </p>
    <div class="box">

<h2>Speed formula</h2>

<p>To calculate the speed of an object, we use the formula:</p>

<p><b>Speed = distance / time</b></p>

<p>This can be written as a formula triangle.</p>
<title>Image in html</title>
<img decoding="async" width="229" height="199" src="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Compound-Measures-image-1.png" alt="Compound Measures image 1" class="wp-image-136281">

<p>
            In simple terms, speed answers the question:
            <strong>“How much distance is covered per unit of time?”</strong>
        </p>

        <div class="formula-box">
            Speed = Distance ÷ Time

            <h3>Explanation</h3>
        <p>
            If an object travels a large distance in a short amount of time,
            it has a high speed.
        </p>
        <p>
            If it travels a small distance over a long time,
            it has a low speed.
        </p>
        <p>
            Speed can be measured in:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>m/s (metres per second)</li>
            <li>km/h (kilometres per hour)</li>
        </ul>

        <hr>
        </div>

 <div class="diagram-box">

    <table>
    <tr>
    <th>Distance</th>
    <th>Time</th>
    <th>Speed</th>
    </tr>

    <tr>
    <td>100 km</td>
    <td>2 hours</td>
    <td>50 km/h</td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
    <td>200 m</td>
    <td>20 s</td>
    <td>10 m/s</td>
    </tr>

    <tr>
    <td>60 km</td>
    <td>1 hour</td>
    <td>60 km/h</td>
    </tr>

    </table>
  </div>
    </section>
    
    <section>
    <header><div class="formulaSX">
    <h2>Formula For Speed</h2>
    <p>Here we will learn about the formula for speed including understanding and using the terms constant speed and average speed.
      We will also be calculating the average speed of an object given its distance and time.
      This will extend to using and applying the speed formula and solving problems involving the formula for speed.</p>
      <p>There are also worksheets on the formula for speed distance and time based on Edexcel, AQA and OCR exam questions, along with further guidance on where to go next if you’re still stuck.</p>
      <div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow"><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-what-is-the-formula-for-speed">What is the formula for speed?</h2>



<p></p>



<p>The<strong> formula for speed </strong>is given by</p>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Speed </strong><span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext mathvariant="bold">=</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> \textbf{=} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.3911em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord textbf">=</span></span></span></span></span></span><strong> distance </strong><span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext mathvariant="bold">÷</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> \textbf{÷} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7667em; vertical-align: -0.1333em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord textbf">÷</span></span></span></span></span></span><strong> time</strong></p>



<p></p>



<p><em>“Speed equals distance divided by time”</em></p>



<p></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-medium"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="298" height="300" src="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Image-1-298x300.png" alt="Formula For Speed Image 1" class="wp-image-122208" srcset="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Image-1-298x300.png 298w, https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Image-1-150x150.png 150w, https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Image-1.png 464w" sizes="(max-width: 298px) 100vw, 298px"></figure>



<p>You will normally shorten this to the below:</p>



<p></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-medium is-style-default"><img decoding="async" width="298" height="300" src="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Image-2-298x300.png" alt="Formula For Speed Image 2" class="wp-image-122207" srcset="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Image-2-298x300.png 298w, https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Image-2-150x150.png 150w, https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Image-2.png 464w" sizes="(max-width: 298px) 100vw, 298px"></figure>



<p>The speed of an object is travelling at is related to the distance it is covering in relation to how long it was travelling for (time).</p>



<p></p>

</div>

</div>
</div>
   </div>
    <div class="formula-boxS">
            <h1>What is speed?</h1>
        <p><strong>Speed</strong> is about how fast an object moves. The speed of the moving object is found by calculating the relationship between the distance the object travels and the period of time taken to travel the distance.</p>
        <p><strong>Some examples of the units of speed are:</strong></p>
        <p>.Metres per second (m/s)</p>
        <p>.Kilometres per hour (km/h)</p>
        <p>.Miles per hour (mph)</p>
        <p>.Speed of sound (343 m/s)</p>
        <p>.Speed of light (299,792,458 m/s)</p>
        <ul>
            <li>m/s (metres per second)</li>
            <li>km/h (kilometres per hour)</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Constant speed</strong> is where the speed does not change, e.g. a straight line on a distance-time graph indicates a constant speed.</p>
        <p>We can calculate the<strong> average speed</strong>of an object by dividing the total distance by the total time taken.</p>
        <p>If you also consider the direction of the movement as well at its speed then this is called the object’s<strong> velocity</strong>.</p>

        <hr>
        </div>
        <div class="formula-box">
            <h2>What is time?</h2>
        <p><strong>Time</strong> can be defined as the ongoing sequence of events taking place.</p>
        <P><strong>Some examples of the units of time are:</strong></P>
        <ul>
            <li>. Secounds (sec)</li>
            <li>. Minutes (mins)</li>
            <li>. Hours (hrs)</li>
            <li>. Days</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>NOTE:</strong> The SI unit(Standard Unit Measurement) for time is the second (s).</p>

        <hr>
        </div>
        </div>
        <div class="formula-box">
            <h3>What is distance?</h3>
        <p><strong>Distance</strong>  is the length of space between two points.</p>
        <P><strong>Some examples of the units of distance are:</strong></P>
        <ul>
            <li>. Millimetres (mm)</li>
            <li>. Centimetres (cm)</li>
            <li>. Metres (m)</li>
            <li>. Kilometres (km)</li>
            <li>. Miles (mi)</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>NOTE:</strong> if we only consider how far the object has moved in regards to its starting point this is called <strong>displacement</strong>.</p>

        <hr>
        </div>
</header>
<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow"><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-example-4-using-speed-to-find-another-value">Example 1: using speed to find another value</h3>



<p></p>



<p>Question: Phil is in a running race. Phil runs at an average speed of <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>5</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>s</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 5 \ m/s. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">5</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="mord">/</span><span class="mord mathnormal">s</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p>The race is <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>21</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 21 \ km </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord">21</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">km</span></span></span></span></span> long.</p>



<p></p>



<p>What is the amount of time Phil takes to finish the race?</p>



<p></p>



<p>Give your answer in <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> hours </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">h</span><span class="mord mathnormal">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">rs</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>s</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> minutes. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6595em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">min</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mord mathnormal">es</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>





<p>Speed: <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>5</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 5 \ m/s </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">5</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="mord">/</span><span class="mord mathnormal">s</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p><br>Distance: <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>21</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 21 \ km </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord">21</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">km</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p><br>Time: unknown</p>





<p></p>





<p>The question used two different units of distance, you need to convert one so you are working with equivalent distances. In this question it is easier to convert <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>21</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 21 \ km </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord">21</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">km</span></span></span></span></span> to <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> m. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.4306em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p><br><span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>21</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>m</mi><mo>×</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>21000</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 21 \ km \times 100=21000 \ m </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7778em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord">21</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">km</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">×</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class="mord">100</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class="mord">21000</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p><br>Because you now have equivalent units of distances you can calculate Phil’s time before converting to <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> hours </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">h</span><span class="mord mathnormal">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">rs</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>s</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> minutes. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6595em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">min</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mord mathnormal">es</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>





<p></p>





<span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Speed&nbsp;</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>&nbsp;distance&nbsp;</mtext><mo>÷</mo><mtext>&nbsp;time</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> \text{Speed } = \text{ distance } \div \text{ time} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Speed&nbsp;</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7778em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">&nbsp;distance&nbsp;</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">÷</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6679em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">&nbsp;time</span></span></span></span></span></span>





<p></p>





<p>We are finding the time. We need to adapt the speed formula.</p>



<p><br></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-medium"><img decoding="async" width="298" height="300" src="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Example-4-Step-4-298x300.png" alt="Formula For Speed Example 4 Step 4" class="wp-image-122205" srcset="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Example-4-Step-4-298x300.png 298w, https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Example-4-Step-4-150x150.png 150w, https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Example-4-Step-4.png 464w" sizes="(max-width: 298px) 100vw, 298px"></figure>



<span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mtable rowspacing="0.25em" columnalign="right left" columnspacing="0em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mtext>Time&nbsp;</mtext></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow><mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mtext>&nbsp;distance&nbsp;</mtext><mo>÷</mo><mtext>&nbsp;speed&nbsp;</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mtext>Time&nbsp;</mtext></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow><mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>21000</mn><mi>m</mi><mo>÷</mo><mn>5</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mtext>Time&nbsp;</mtext></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow><mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>4200</mn><mtext>&nbsp;seconds&nbsp;</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> \begin{aligned} \text {Time }&amp;=\text { distance } \div \text { speed } \\\\ \text {Time }&amp;=21000 m \div 5 \ m/ s \\\\ \text {Time }&amp;=4200 \text { seconds }  \end{aligned} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 7.5em; vertical-align: -3.5em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mtable"><span class="col-align-r"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 4em;"><span class="" style="top: -6.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Time&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -4.66em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Time&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -1.66em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -0.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Time&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 3.5em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="col-align-l"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 4em;"><span class="" style="top: -6.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">&nbsp;distance&nbsp;</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">÷</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">&nbsp;speed&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord">21000</span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">÷</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mord">5</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="mord">/</span><span class="mord mathnormal">s</span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -0.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord">4200</span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">&nbsp;seconds&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 3.5em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>





<p></p>





<p>You have calculated the time to be <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>4200</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>s</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>s</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 4200 \ seconds. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord">4200</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">seco</span><span class="mord mathnormal">n</span><span class="mord mathnormal">d</span><span class="mord mathnormal">s</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p><br>However the question wants the time in <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>h</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> hours </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">h</span><span class="mord mathnormal">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">rs</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>s</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> minutes, </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.854em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">min</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mord mathnormal">es</span><span class="mpunct">,</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p><br>Remember: <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>s</mi><mo>÷</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> seconds \div 60 = minutes </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7778em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">seco</span><span class="mord mathnormal">n</span><span class="mord mathnormal">d</span><span class="mord mathnormal">s</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">÷</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class="mord">60</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6595em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal">min</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mord mathnormal">es</span></span></span></span></span> </p>



<p></p>



<p><br><span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>4200</mn><mo>÷</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>70</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 4200 \div 60=70 \ minutes </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7278em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord">4200</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">÷</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class="mord">60</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6595em;"></span><span class="mord">70</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">min</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mord mathnormal">es</span></span></span></span></span> </p>



<p></p>



<p><br>Therefore</p>



<p></p>



<p><br><span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>70</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>s</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  70 \ minutes=1 \ hr </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6595em;"></span><span class="mord">70</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">min</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mord mathnormal">es</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord">1</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">h</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0278em;">r</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>10</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex">  10 mins </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6595em;"></span><span class="mord">10</span><span class="mord mathnormal">min</span><span class="mord mathnormal">s</span></span></span></span></span> </p>



<p></p>



<p><br>Therefore</p>



<p></p>



<p><br>Phil completes the race in <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>h</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 1 \ hour </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord">1</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">h</span><span class="mord mathnormal">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0278em;">r</span></span></span></span></span>  and <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>10</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 10 \ minutes </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6595em;"></span><span class="mord">10</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">min</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mord mathnormal">es</span></span></span></span></span> </p>


</div>
</div>
<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow"><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-example-5-using-speed-to-find-another-value">Example 2: using speed to find another value</h3>



<p></p>



<p>Question: A train travels at <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>120</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 120 \ km/h </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">120</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">km</span><span class="mord">/</span><span class="mord mathnormal">h</span></span></span></span></span> for <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>h</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>s</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 3\frac{1}{4} \ hours. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1901em; vertical-align: -0.345em;"></span><span class="mord">3</span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8451em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.655em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">4</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.394em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.345em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">h</span><span class="mord mathnormal">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">rs</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span> Calculate the total distance travelled. 
</p>



<p></p>





<p>Speed: <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>120</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 120 \ km/h </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">120</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">km</span><span class="mord">/</span><span class="mord mathnormal">h</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p><br>Distance: unknown</p>



<p></p>



<p><br>Time: <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>h</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>s</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3.25</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>h</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 3\frac{1}{4} \ hours=3.25 \ hours </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1901em; vertical-align: -0.345em;"></span><span class="mord">3</span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8451em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.655em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">4</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.394em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.345em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">h</span><span class="mord mathnormal">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">rs</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord">3.25</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">h</span><span class="mord mathnormal">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal">u</span><span class="mord mathnormal">rs</span></span></span></span></span></p>





<p></p>





<p>The units align. Sometime people prefer decimals to fractions, so we can use <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>3</mn><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 3\frac{1}{4} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1901em; vertical-align: -0.345em;"></span><span class="mord">3</span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8451em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.655em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">4</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.394em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.345em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span></span></span></span></span> or <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>3.25</mn></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 3.25 </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class="mord">3.25</span></span></span></span></span></p>





<p></p>





<span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Speed&nbsp;</mtext><mo>=</mo><mtext>&nbsp;distance&nbsp;</mtext><mo>÷</mo><mtext>&nbsp;time</mtext></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> \text{Speed } = \text{ distance } \div \text{ time} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Speed&nbsp;</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7778em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">&nbsp;distance&nbsp;</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">÷</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6679em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">&nbsp;time</span></span></span></span></span></span>





<p></p>





<p>We are finding the time. We need to adapt the speed formula.</p>



<p><br></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-medium is-style-default"><img decoding="async" width="298" height="300" src="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Example-5-Step-4-298x300.png" alt="Formula For Speed Example 5 Step 4" class="wp-image-122204" srcset="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Example-5-Step-4-298x300.png 298w, https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Example-5-Step-4-150x150.png 150w, https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/Formula-For-Speed-Example-5-Step-4.png 464w" sizes="(max-width: 298px) 100vw, 298px"></figure>



<span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mtable rowspacing="0.25em" columnalign="right left" columnspacing="0em"><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mtext>Distance&nbsp;</mtext></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow><mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mtext>speed</mtext><mo>×</mo><mtext>time</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mtext>Distance&nbsp;</mtext></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow><mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>120</mn><mtext>&nbsp;km/h</mtext><mo>×</mo><mn>3.25</mn><mtext>&nbsp;hours</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mtext>Distance&nbsp;</mtext></mstyle></mtd><mtd><mstyle scriptlevel="0" displaystyle="true"><mrow><mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>390</mn><mtext>&nbsp;km&nbsp;</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mtd></mtr></mtable><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> \begin{aligned} \text {Distance }&amp;=\text {speed} \times \text {time} \\\\ \text {Distance }&amp;=120 \  \text{km/h}  \times  3.25\ \text{hours} \\\\ \text {Distance }&amp;=390 \text { km } \end{aligned} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 7.5em; vertical-align: -3.5em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mtable"><span class="col-align-r"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 4em;"><span class="" style="top: -6.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Distance&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -4.66em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Distance&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -1.66em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -0.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Distance&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 3.5em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="col-align-l"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 4em;"><span class="" style="top: -6.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">speed</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">×</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">time</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord">120</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">km/h</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">×</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mord">3.25</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">hours</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -0.16em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord"></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mord">390</span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">&nbsp;km&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 3.5em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>





<p></p>





<p>You have calculated the time to be <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>390</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>s</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 390 \ kilometres. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord">390</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">ki</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0197em;">l</span><span class="mord mathnormal">o</span><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="mord mathnormal">e</span><span class="mord mathnormal">t</span><span class="mord mathnormal">res</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>



<p></p>



<p><br>Therefore the distance of the journey is <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>390</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>m</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 390 \ km. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6944em;"></span><span class="mord">390</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">km</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>


</div>
</div>
  </section>

   <section>
