<section id="density" class="topic-section">
    <section>
    <header class="formulaS">
    <h2>DENSITY</h2>
    <p>Density is a compound measure that shows how much mass is contained
    within a given volume.</p>
    <p>
    It tells us how tightly packed the particles are in a material.
</p>

<p><strong>Density</strong> measures how compact a material is.</p>

    </header>
    <p>
It compares the <strong>mass of an object</strong> with the <strong>volume it occupies</strong>.
Heavy materials packed into a small space have a higher density.
</p>
<p>Common units for density include, grams per cubic centimetre 
(
g
/
c
m
3
)
(g/cm 
3
 ) and kilograms per cubic metre 
(
k
g
/
m
3
)
.
(kg/m 
3
 ).</p>
 <p><strong>Density Formula</strong></p>
 <P>To calculate the density of an object, we use the density formula,</P>
 <p><strong>Density = Mass ÷ Volume</strong></p>
 <p>This can be written as a formula triangle.</p>

 <title>Image in html</title>
 <img decoding="async" width="229" height="199" src="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Compound-Measures-image-2.png" alt="Compound Measures image 2" class="wp-image-136282">

 <div class="formula-box">
    <h1> Mass Density Volume</h1>
    <p>Here we will learn about mass, density and volume, including what they are and how they are related to each other.</p>
    <p>There are also mass density volume worksheets based on Edexcel, AQA and OCR exam questions, along with further guidance on where to go next if you’re still stuck.</p>
</div>
<h2>what is Mass Density Volume?</h2>
<P>Mass, density and volume are physical properties of objects.</P>

<P><strong>Mass</strong> is the measurement of the amount of matter there is in an object. The units of mass are usually kilograms 
(
k
g
)
(kg) or grams 
(
g
)
.
(g). The<strong>kilogram</strong> is the SI unit (the International System of Units) for mass.</P>
<P><strong>Volume</strong> is a measure of how much space an object takes up. The volume of a substance is often measured in cubic centimetres 
(
c
m
3
)
.
(cm 
3
). The derived SI unit for volume is the <strong>cubic metre </strong>
(
m
3
)
.
(m 
3
 ).

</P>
<P><strong>Density</strong> is a compound measure made from the ratio of mass and volume. Density is a measure of the amount of matter there is per unit volume. The SI unit for density is<strong> kilograms per cubic metre </strong> 
(
k
g
/
m
3
)
.
(kg/m 
3
 ).</P>
 <p>Imagine there are two objects the same size. The first object has high density, the second object has a lower density. The object with high density would feel heavier than the object with the lower density.</p>
 <p>You could try this with two water bottles. Fill one with water and fill the other with air.</p>
 <p>The density of water is approximately 
1000
 
k
g
/
m
3
.
1000 kg/m 
3
 .

</p>
<p>The density of air is approximately 
1.225
 
k
g
/
m
3
.
1.225 kg/m 
3
 .</p>
 <p>If an object has a large mass but small volume, it has a high density.</p>
<p>
    If it has a small mass but large volume, it has a low density.
</p>
<p>Common units include:</p>
<ul>
    <li>g/cm³</li>
    <li>kg/m³</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<div class="diagram-box">

<table>

<tr>
<th>Mass</th>
<th>Volume</th>
<th>Density</th>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>500 g</td>
<td>100 cm³</td>
<td>5 g/cm³</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td>800 g</td>
<td>200 cm³</td>
<td>4 g/cm³</td>
</tr>

</table>

<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow"><h3 class="wp-block-heading">Density</h3>



<p></p>



<p>To calculate the mass, density or volume of an object, we use the formula:</p>



<p></p>



<span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Density</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mtext>Mass</mtext><mtext>Volume</mtext></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> \text{Density}=\frac{\text{Mass}}{\text{Volume}} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Density</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.2173em; vertical-align: -0.345em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8723em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.655em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord text mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Volume</span></span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.394em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord text mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Mass</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.345em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span></span></span></span></span>



<p></p>



<p>This can be written as a formula triangle:</p>



<p></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full is-resized"><img decoding="async" width="304" height="264" src="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Mass-density-volume-image-1.png" alt="Mass density volume image 1" class="wp-image-126858" style="width:180px" srcset="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Mass-density-volume-image-1.png 304w, https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Mass-density-volume-image-1-300x261.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 304px) 100vw, 304px"></figure>



<p></p>



<p>where <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> M </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.109em;">M</span></span></span></span></span> is the mass, <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> D </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0278em;">D</span></span></span></span></span> is the density, and <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> V </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;">V</span></span></span></span></span> is the volume of an object.</p>



<p></p>



<p>Using this triangle, we can show:</p>



<p></p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>D</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> M=D\times{V} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.109em;">M</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7667em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0278em;">D</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">×</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;">V</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>



<li><span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>÷</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> D=M\div{V} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0278em;">D</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7667em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.109em;">M</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">÷</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;">V</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>



<li><span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>÷</mo><mi>D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> V=M\div{D} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;">V</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7667em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.109em;">M</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">÷</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0278em;">D</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>
</ul>



<p></p>



<p>Note: The <strong>relative density</strong>, or <strong>specific gravity</strong> is the relationship between the density of a substance in relation to the density of another referenced substance. </p>



<p></p>



<p>For example, water at <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><msup><mn>4</mn><mi>o</mi></msup><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 4^{o}C </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">4</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.6644em;"><span class="" style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mathnormal mtight">o</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0715em;">C</span></span></span></span></span> has a density of <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn><mi>k</mi><mi>g</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>l</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 1kg/l. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">1</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0315em;">k</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0359em;">g</span><span class="mord">/</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0197em;">l</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span> Liquid mercury has a density of <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>13.6</mn><mi>k</mi><mi>g</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 13.6kg/l </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">13.6</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0315em;">k</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0359em;">g</span><span class="mord">/</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0197em;">l</span></span></span></span></span> and so its specific gravity is <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>13.6</mn></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 13.6 </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class="mord">13.6</span></span></span></span></span> as <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>13.6</mn><mo>÷</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>13.6.</mn></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 13.6\div{1}=13.6. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.7278em; vertical-align: -0.0833em;"></span><span class="mord">13.6</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span><span class="mbin">÷</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2222em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mord">1</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class="mord">13.6.</span></span></span></span></span> As both units are in <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>g</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><mi>l</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> kg/l, </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0315em;">k</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0359em;">g</span><span class="mord">/</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0197em;">l</span><span class="mpunct">,</span></span></span></span></span> specific gravity has no units.</p>
</div>
</div>

</div>
<h3>Worked Examples</h3>

<title>Image in html</title>
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow"><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-example-1-calculating-the-density-g-cm-3">Example 1: calculating the density <tnr>(g/cm<sup>3</sup>)</tnr></h3>



<p></p>



<p>A sphere is made from gold. It has volume <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>3</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>c</mi><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 3 \ cm^3 </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8141em;"></span><span class="mord">3</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal">c</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8141em;"><span class="" style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and mass <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>60</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>g</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 60 \ g. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8389em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord">60</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0359em;">g</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span> Calculate the density of the object.</p>



<p></p>



<ol class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Write the formula with the correct subject.</strong></li>
</ol>



<p></p>



<p>To calculate the density, we would need to divide the mass of the object by the volume of the object.</p>



<p></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="304" height="264" src="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Mass-density-volume-flip-card-2.png" alt="Mass density volume flip card 2" class="wp-image-126856" srcset="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Mass-density-volume-flip-card-2.png 304w, https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Mass-density-volume-flip-card-2-300x261.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 304px) 100vw, 304px"></figure>



<p></p>



<span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Density</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mtext>Mass</mtext><mtext>Volume</mtext></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> \text{Density}=\frac{\text{Mass}}{\text{Volume}} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Density</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.2173em; vertical-align: -0.345em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8723em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.655em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord text mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Volume</span></span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.394em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord text mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Mass</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.345em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span></span></span></span></span>



<p></p>



<p></p>



<p><span class="is-counter">2</span><strong>Substitute known values into the formula and do the calculation.</strong></p>



<p></p>



<span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Density</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mtext>Mass</mtext><mtext>Volume</mtext></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>60</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> \text{Density}=\frac{\text{Mass}}{\text{Volume}}=\frac{60}{3}=20 </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Density</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.2173em; vertical-align: -0.345em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8723em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.655em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord text mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Volume</span></span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.394em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord text mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Mass</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.345em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1901em; vertical-align: -0.345em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8451em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.655em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.394em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">60</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.345em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class="mord">20</span></span></span></span></span>



<p></p>



<p></p>



<p><span class="is-counter">3</span><strong> Write down the solution including the units.</strong></p>


<p></p>



<p>The density of the object is <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>20</mn><msup><mtext>&nbsp;g/cm</mtext><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 20\text{ g/cm}^{3} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.204em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">20</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">&nbsp;g/cm</span></span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.954em;"><span class="" style="top: -3.2029em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>

</div>

<div class="wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class="wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow"><h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-example-2-calculating-the-density-kg-m-3">Example 2: calculating the density <tnr>(kg/m<sup>3</sup>)</tnr></h3>



<p></p>



<p>An object is made from steel. It has a volume of <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>25</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 25 \ m^3 </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8141em;"></span><span class="mord">25</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8141em;"><span class="" style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and a mass of <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>425</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>g</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 425 \ kg. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8889em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord">425</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0315em;">k</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0359em;">g</span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span> Calculate the density of the object.</p>



<p></p>





<p>To calculate the density, we need to divide the mass of the object by the volume of the object.</p>



<p><br></p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="304" height="264" src="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Mass-density-volume-example-2.png" alt="Mass density volume example 2" class="wp-image-126850" srcset="https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Mass-density-volume-example-2.png 304w, https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Mass-density-volume-example-2-300x261.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 304px) 100vw, 304px"></figure>



<p></p>



<p><br><span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Density</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mtext>Mass</mtext><mtext>Volume</mtext></mfrac></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> \text{Density}=\frac{\text{Mass}}{\text{Volume}} </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Density</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.2173em; vertical-align: -0.345em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8723em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.655em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord text mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Volume</span></span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.394em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord text mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Mass</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.345em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>





<p></p>





<span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Density</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mtext>Mass</mtext><mtext>Volume</mtext></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>425</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> \text{Density}=\frac{\text{Mass}}{\text{Volume}}=\frac{425}{25}=17 </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;"></span><span class="mord text"><span class="mord">Density</span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.2173em; vertical-align: -0.345em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8723em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.655em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord text mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Volume</span></span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.394em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord text mtight"><span class="mord mtight">Mass</span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.345em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.1901em; vertical-align: -0.345em;"></span><span class="mord"><span class="mopen nulldelimiter"></span><span class="mfrac"><span class="vlist-t vlist-t2"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8451em;"><span class="" style="top: -2.655em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">25</span></span></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.23em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="frac-line" style="border-bottom-width: 0.04em;"></span></span><span class="" style="top: -3.394em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 3em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">425</span></span></span></span></span><span class="vlist-s">​</span></span><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.345em;"><span class=""></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mclose nulldelimiter"></span></span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span><span class="mrel">=</span><span class="mspace" style="margin-right: 0.2778em;"></span></span><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 0.6444em;"></span><span class="mord">17</span></span></span></span></span>





<p></p>





<p>The density of the object made of steel is <span class="katex-eq katex-rendered" data-katex-display="false"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mn>17</mn><mtext>&nbsp;</mtext><mi>k</mi><mi>g</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">/</mi><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">.</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 17 \ kg/m^{3}. </annotation></semantics></math></span><span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"><span class="base"><span class="strut" style="height: 1.0641em; vertical-align: -0.25em;"></span><span class="mord">17</span><span class="mspace">&nbsp;</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0315em;">k</span><span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right: 0.0359em;">g</span><span class="mord">/</span><span class="mord"><span class="mord mathnormal">m</span><span class="msupsub"><span class="vlist-t"><span class="vlist-r"><span class="vlist" style="height: 0.8141em;"><span class="" style="top: -3.063em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span class="pstrut" style="height: 2.7em;"></span><span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"><span class="mord mtight"><span class="mord mtight">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="mord">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>


