<td>20 N/m²</td>
</tr>

</table>

</div>

<div class="formula-box">
<h3>Pressure Force Area</h3>
<p>Here we will learn about pressure, force and area, including what they are and how they are related to one another.</p>
<p>There are also pressure force area worksheets based on Edexcel, AQA and OCR exam questions, along with further guidance on where to go next if you’re still stuck.</p>
</div>
    <h1>Area</h1>
    <p><strong>Area</strong> is a measure of the size of space a flat shape takes up. The SI unit for area is the <strong>metre squared</strong> (
m
2
)
(m 
2
 ) although we can use other units including square centimetres 
(
c
m
2
