 <p>Imagine an elephant standing on 
4 legs. The pressure applied to the ground is distributed over a wider area than if the elephant was standing on one leg. This is because the force remains constant (the weight of the elephant), but the area in which the force is applied has decreased, so the pressure increases. This is an example of inverse proportion.</p>
